# NOTE (2026-06-23): Vercel Git LFS support is now ENABLED on this project
# (https://vercel.com/changelog/git-lfs-support) — Vercel resolves LFS pointers at build time and
# serves the real binaries, so LFS-tracked files DO deploy correctly now. The de-LFS rules below are
# kept because they still work AND regular blobs sidestep the flaky-network LFS *upload* problem
# (see docs/DEPLOY.md), NOT because Vercel can't serve LFS. Files >100 MB must stay LFS (GitHub's
# regular-blob limit) and now deploy fine once the LFS object reaches the remote.
# (History: before this, Vercel served LFS as a ~133-byte pointer -> 404/crash, so the deploy-served
# binaries below — *.unityweb, StreamingAssets/*.glb, and public/da-hilg/ GLBs — were de-LFS'd.)
public/da-hilg/*.glb filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Deploy-critical R3F playable-character meshes (all < 3MB): keep as REGULAR git blobs (NOT LFS) so
# Vercel serves real GLBs. xq.glb is intentionally NOT here: at 126MB it exceeds GitHub's 100MB
# per-file limit, so it stays LFS like the other large level assets (level/canyon/meemaw/stanton).
public/da-hilg/cece.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto
public/da-hilg/drew.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto
public/da-hilg/kelli.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto
public/da-hilg/mike.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto

# Deploy-critical R3F animation clips: served at runtime, must be REGULAR git blobs (NOT LFS).
public/da-hilg/anims/*.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto

# Deploy-served LEVEL meshes that now fit under GitHub's 100MB limit (xq/canyon/stanton/meemaw
# dropped well below 100MB once the Google photoreal mesh was removed): de-LFS so Vercel serves
# real bytes instead of a 133-byte pointer. dahill (level.glb) is still ~170MB > 100MB, so it must
# stay in LFS until its facade-atlas textures are trimmed under the limit.
public/da-hilg/xq.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto
public/da-hilg/canyon.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto
public/da-hilg/stanton.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto
public/da-hilg/meemaw.glb -filter -diff -merge text=auto

# Uncompressed editable LEVEL masters (exports/<slug>/<slug>.level.glb): large (~130MB, over GitHub's
# 100MB limit) and NOT deploy-served (only the compressed public/da-hilg + StreamingAssets assets are),
# so the Vercel-can't-resolve-LFS constraint doesn't apply. LFS so the flaky push chunks/resumes.
exports/*/*.level.glb filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

src/assets/anim/kelli-mx-anims.glb filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
unity/DaHilgUnity/Assets/DaHilg/Art/Levels/*.glb filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Non-deployed local Mixamo animation archive (~168MB, 2344 clips): keep in LFS so the flaky push
# chunks/resumes and these never bloat git history. Never served to any deploy.
mixamo-animation-library/**/*.glb filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
